"script": "Press the handle, and your toilet empties itself in seconds with no pump at all. So how does it suck everything down? Well, hidden behind the bowl is a curved tube shaped like an upside-down U, called the siphon. When you flush, water rushes in fast and fills that tube completely. Then gravity drags the water down the long side, and this pulls the bowl water up and over the bend with it. The whole bowl empties until air finally breaks the chain, making that gurgle you hear at the end every single time.",
